The paper deals with computer vision and reasoning about images/objects, which suggests it belongs to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of graphs and convolutional neural networks also suggests it could belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The consideration of intrinsic characteristics and attention mechanisms suggests it could also belong to the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category. Finally, the evaluation of supervised and semi-supervised approaches suggests it could belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
